    <item>
      <title>Félix de Augusta: Nidolke dəŋu Dios ñi Nùtram</title>
      <link>https://benmolineaux.github.io/bookshelf/core-texts/augustadios/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 03 Feb 1903 16:45:54 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://benmolineaux.github.io/bookshelf/core-texts/augustadios/</guid>
      <description>Transcribed
This translation was produced by Fr. Félix de Augusta for Mapuche children in the Catholic Schools which were run by the Capuchin order in Chile. It is a version of &amp;ldquo;Compendio de la Historia Sagrada&amp;rdquo; (a compendium of sacred history) by Dr. D. Federich Knecht, Archbishop of Freiburg. The translation is a version of the Spanish text edited by D. Vicente Ortí y Escolano.
Spelling, according to Augusta&amp;rsquo;s introduction, follows Rudolf Lenz&amp;rsquo;s principles for the language.</description>
